&lt;p&gt;Sunday 29th November 2020 or if sufficient numbers are reached.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsible to&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Line Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accountable to &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Healthy Child Programme Team Leader (HCPTL)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an enthusiastic nurse, ready for a challenge? We are looking for new staff to join our dynamic teams of SCPHN (Specialised Community Public Health Nurses), School Health Assistants (SHA’s) and Health Mentors (HM’s). Working together we can make a real difference to outcomes for children and families in the Tameside area, reducing health inequalities across the borough.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The role offers scope for you to develop professionally and contribute to a responsive and busy service. You will work closely with the specialist SCPHN-SN (School Nurses) with an allocated caseload. There are opportunities for autonomous working as part of an integrated skill mix team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a corporate team structure that covers a defined geographical and you will deliver the Integrated 0 – 19 Healthy Child Programme through multi-agency working with our partners in Education, social care, voluntary agencies and the wider community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the lively city of Manchester to the west and the Pennines to the east, Tameside offers a great variety of experience in terms of population, demographics and communities. Training and development is highly valued and we can offer excellent in-house expertise including safeguarding, immunisation and team development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive a full induction, preceptorship, safeguarding supervision, and clinical supervision, as well as role specific training. As an Integrated Care NHS Foundation Trust, there will be continued opportunities to develop shared service delivery with partner agencies, using evidence based assessments and interventions. There will also be an opportunity for you to support delivery of the National Immunisation Programme with appropriate training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are based in the Tameside area. Applicants must have their own vehicle available for work use. This post will be subject to a probationary period. Previous unsuccessful applicants need not apply. This advert may close at short notice if sufficient numbers are met.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For all posts successful applicants will be subject to an enhanced Disclosure and Barring Bureau Service check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
